<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1045,2045]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,153,251]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1946,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ehlers, 1887" authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1887" box="[321,661,1946,1972]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="articulata">
<emphasis box="[321,510,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Nereis articulata</emphasis>
Ehlers, 1887
</taxonomicName>
, a senior homonym, has been considered invalid. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder, G." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="37 - 59" refId="ref20213" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1985) Revision der Gattung Ceratonereis Kinberg (Nereididae, Polychaeta) (Mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Arten mit enigeschnittenem Prostomium). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 82, 37 - 59." type="journal article" year="1985">Hartmann-Schröder (1985)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kinberg, 1865" authorityName="Kinberg" authorityYear="1865" box="[644,959,1981,2009]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Ceratonereis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,789,1983,2009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ceratonereis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kinberg, J. G. H." box="[797,959,1981,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref20665" refString="Kinberg, J. G. H. (1865) Annulata nova. [Continuatio.]. Ofversigt af Koniglich Vetenskapsakademiens forhandlingar, Stockholm, 22 (2), 167 - 179." type="journal article" year="1865">Kinberg, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and placed it in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1985" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1985" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Composetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,1983,2009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Composetia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder, G." box="[151,448,2017,2044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="37 - 59" refId="ref20213" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1985) Revision der Gattung Ceratonereis Kinberg (Nereididae, Polychaeta) (Mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Arten mit enigeschnittenem Prostomium). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 82, 37 - 59." type="journal article" year="1985">Hartmann-Schröder, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as it has notopodial homogomph falcigers. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bakken, T. &amp; Wilson, R. S." box="[1079,1369,2017,2044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="507 - 547" refId="ref19914" refString="Bakken, T. &amp; Wilson, R. S. (2005) Phylogeny of nereidids (Polychaeta, Nereididae) with paragnaths. Zoologica Scripta, 34 (5), 507 - 547. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2005.00200. x" type="journal article" year="2005">Bakken &amp; Wilson (2005)</bibRefCitation>
com- mented that members of that subgenus do not have notopodial homogomph falcigers. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hsueh, 2020" authorityName="Hsueh" authorityYear="2020" box="[1102,1290,153,179]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="articulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1102,1290,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nereis articulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1297,1358,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1297,1358,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be readily distinguished from the other 35 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[599,671,190,215]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[599,671,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nereis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1035,189,215]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">East Asia</collectingCountry>
and the present study by having an articulated tentacular cirri, which is not seen in other congeners.
</paragraph>
